[0.000, "o", "\r\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\r\nв–¶ Pretend we closed the terminal and opened a NEW session (no in-session state)\r\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\r\nвЂ¦new shell, zero contextвЂ¦\r\n\r\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\r\nв–¶ SESSION 2 вЂ” it remembers across sessions\r\nв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђв•ђ\r\n$ .venv/bin/mnemo ask how do we store auth tokens and why?\r\n"]
[681.769, "o", "вЂє LLM: qwen2.5:7b В· embeddings: fastembed (local)\r\nв•­в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Q: how do we store auth tokens and why? в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•®\r\nв”‚ From the provided information, we can infer several key points about         в”‚\r\nв”‚ security practices and memory abstractions:                                  в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ ### Security Practices:                                                      в”‚\r\nв”‚ 1. **JWT in HttpOnly Cookies:**                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚    - We use JWT in httpOnly cookies to ensure that they are not accessible   в”‚\r\nв”‚ through client-side JavaScript. This helps mitigate risks associated with    в”‚\r\nв”‚ XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) attacks where an attacker might exploit a         в”‚\r\nв”‚ vulnerability to steal session tokens from the user's browser.               в”‚\r\nв”‚                                 "]
[0.000, "o", "                                             в”‚\r\nв”‚ 2. **Not Used in LocalStorage:**                                             в”‚\r\nв”‚    - JSON Web Tokens (JWT) are explicitly mentioned as not being used within в”‚\r\nв”‚ `localStorage`, highlighting the preference for keeping sensitive            в”‚\r\nв”‚ information such as session data out of client-side storage that is more     в”‚\r\nв”‚ accessible and potentially exploitable by malicious scripts.                 в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ 3. **HttpOnly Cookie Implementation:**                                       в”‚\r\nв”‚    - HttpOnly cookies prevent JavaScript on the client side from accessing   в”‚\r\nв”‚ the cookie, which can be useful in preventing certain kinds of XSS attacks.  в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ 4. **Token Abstraction:**                                                    в”‚\r\nв”‚    - JWTs are mentioned "]
[0.000, "o", "as tokens used to secure cookies and help enhance    в”‚\r\nв”‚ security by not storing sensitive data directly in `localStorage`.           в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ ### Memory Abstractions:                                                     в”‚\r\nв”‚ 1. **MemoryBackend Protocol:**                                               в”‚\r\nв”‚    - The protocol for a pluggable long-term memory engine is discussed,      в”‚\r\nв”‚ which includes methods such as remembering, recalling, consolidating, and    в”‚\r\nв”‚ forgetting data.                                                             в”‚\r\nв”‚    - This suggests a flexible system that can adapt to different backends as в”‚\r\nв”‚ needed.                                                                      в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ 2. **CogneeAdapter:**                                                        в”‚\r\nв”‚    - A Cognee AD"]
[0.000, "o", "APTER class is described that implements the `MemoryBackend` в”‚\r\nв”‚ protocol by delegating calls to Cognee's V2 engine.                          в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ 3. **Interface Implementation:**                                             в”‚\r\nв”‚    - The implementation uses the interface `MemoryBackend` which provides a  в”‚\r\nв”‚ standardized way to interact with different memory engines.                  в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ 4. **RememberOutcome Class:**                                                в”‚\r\nв”‚    - This class represents the summary of a store operation, giving us       в”‚\r\nв”‚ insight into how operations are tracked and summarized in the system after   в”‚\r\nв”‚ data is stored.                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ 5. **Mem"]
[0.000, "o", "ory Abstraction Layer:**                                             в”‚\r\nв”‚    - The `memorybackend` interface represents a pluggable long-term memory   в”‚\r\nв”‚ engine which includes storage methods like remembering and recalling.        в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\nв”‚ ### Summary:                                                                 в”‚\r\nв”‚ This document focuses on both security practices and the design of a         в”‚\r\nв”‚ flexible memory system, emphasizing the use of secure cookies (HttpOnly) for в”‚\r\nв”‚ JWT to mitigate XSS risks and providing a structured approach via            в”‚\r\nв”‚ `MemoryBackend` interfaces and classes such as `CogneeAdapter` and           в”‚\r\nв”‚ `RememberOutcome`.                                                           в”‚\r\nв”‚                                                                              в”‚\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "в”‚ These practices highlight a comprehensive approach to securing session data  в”‚\r\nв”‚ while ensuring a robust and flexible architecture that can adapt to          в”‚\r\nв”‚ different memory backend implementations.                                    в”‚\r\nв•°в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв•Ї\r\n"]
